<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-11-21T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-11-21T18:00:00-05:00" n="816" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d816">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">714.1515/978: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hawks</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-11-21T17:00:00-06:00">November 21, 1929—5
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received November 22—12:17
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>150. Referring to the Department’s telegram of November 20, 8 p.m. I
                                conveyed verbally to the Minister for Foreign Affairs the
                                information contained therein and he stated specifically that I
                                could notify the Department that the Government of Guatemala would
                                so instruct its delegate that he will be able to discuss all phases
                                of the problem.</p>
                            <p>Repeated to Honduras.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hawks</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>